<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870729-0027 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:Borden Inc.</HL><DD> 07/29/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> BNEARNINGS (ERN) </IN><TEXT>   Borden Inc., a New York-based producer of dairy, grocery and chemical products, reported second-quarter earnings climbed 21% to a record for any second period of $62.7 million, or 85 cents a share. Sales advanced 30% to $1.60 billion, a record for any quarter. Borden said it is &quot;well on the way toward our projected 20% gain&quot; in 1987 per-share profit. The company said it expects to post $3.60 in full-year profit per share, compared with $223.3 million, or $3 a share, in 1986. Borden cited strong performances by recent acquisitions and better results in most continuing businesses. Borden reported first-half profit rose 20% to $106.7 million, or $1.45 a share. </TEXT></DOC>